The FSDH Group has realised a Profit before Tax (PBT) of N5.57billion for the financial year ended December 31, 2018. This was disclosed by the Chairman of the bank,  Femi Agbaje, at the 7th Annual General Meeting of FSDH Merchant Bank Limited. Agbaje said  the profit represented an increase of 43.93% over the PBT of N3.87billion for the year ended December 31, 2017. Similarly, Profit After Tax (PAT) for the Group increased by 44.95% from N3.27billion for the year ended December 31, 2017 to N4.74billion for the period ended December 31, 2018. Earnings Per Share (EPS) for the Group was 164kobo which is 55kobo higher than the 109kobo that was recorded in the financial year ended December 31, 2016. Agbaje said: “During the period under review all our subsidiaries posted profits. FSDH Asset Management (FSDH-AM) contributed a profit of N327.70million, while Pensions Alliance Limited (PAL) and FSDH Securities (FSDH-SEC) added N1.31billion and N96.16million respectively to the Profit after Tax of the Group. “When compared with the PAT for the year ended December 31, 2017, this translates to an increase of 2.55%, 32.59%, and 103.04% for FSDH-AM, PAL and FSDH-SEC, respectively.” FSDH shareholders’ funds stand at N23.7bn LAGOS: Access Bank records N95bn profit in 2018 FCMB Group announces N170bn gross revenue